articles.title: Google Algorithm Update: February 2026 Core Update Rolling Out
articles.description: Google has begun rolling out a major core algorithm update affecting search rankings globally. Early data shows significant fluctuations in rankings across multiple industries.

articles.title: Core Web Vitals: New INP Metric Replaces FID
articles.description: Google officially replaces First Input Delay (FID) with Interaction to Next Paint (INP) as a Core Web Vitals metric. Sites need to optimize for faster interactions.

articles.title: SEO Ranking Factors 2026: What Really Matters
articles.description: Our annual study reveals the top ranking factors for 2026. E-E-A-T, user engagement, and AI-generated content detection lead the list.

articles.title: Google Search Console Adds New Performance Insights
articles.description: Search Console now provides deeper insights into page experience, including detailed INP breakdowns and mobile usability improvements.

articles.title: AI-Generated Content: Google's Detection Methods Revealed
articles.description: Internal documents reveal how Google identifies and treats AI-generated content. Quality and originality remain the primary factors.

articles.title: Mobile-First Indexing: Desktop Sites No Longer Crawled
articles.description: Google completes its transition to mobile-first indexing. Desktop-only sites will see significant ranking drops.

articles.title: Local SEO Update: Google Maps Rankings Algorithm Change
articles.description: Major changes to Google Maps ranking algorithm emphasize review velocity, response time, and user engagement metrics.

articles.title: Page Speed Update: New Thresholds for Core Web Vitals
articles.description: Google announces stricter thresholds for LCP, CLS, and INP. Sites must meet new standards by Q3 2026 to maintain rankings.
